data.name: EnhancedCustomShapeExtrusion
desc: This service may be represented by a com.sun.star.beans.PropertyValue [].

properties.name: Brightness
desc: This attribute specifies the brightness of a scene in percent.

properties.name: Depth
desc: The first value of EnhancedCustomShapeParameterPair specifies the depth of the extrusion in 1/100 mm.
The second value (0.0 to 1.0) specifies the fraction of the extrusion that lies before the shape, a value of 0 is default.

properties.name: Diffusion
desc: This attribute specifies the amount of diffusion reflected by the shape in percent.

properties.name: Extrusion
desc: This property specifies if extrusion is displayed.
The default for this property is \"false\"

properties.name: ExtrusionColor
desc: This attribute specifies if the \"SecondFillColor\" is used as extrusion color.

properties.name: FirstLightDirection
desc: Specifies the direction of the first light.

properties.name: FirstLightHarsh
desc: Specifies if the primary light is harsh.

properties.name: FirstLightLevel
desc: Specifies the intensity for the first light in percent.

properties.name: LightFace
desc: Specifies if the front face of the extrusion responds to lightning changes.

properties.name: Metal
desc: Specifies if the surface of the extrusion object looks like metal.

properties.name: NumberOfLineSegments
desc: Specifies the number of line segments that should be used to display curved surfaces.
The higher the number the more line segments are used.

properties.name: Origin
desc: This attribute specifies the origin within the bounding box of the shape in terms of the shape size fractions.

properties.name: ProjectionMode
desc: This property defines the projection mode.

properties.name: RotateAngle
desc: This attributes specifies the rotation angle about the x-axis in grad.
The order of rotation is: z-axis, y-axis and then x-axis. The z-axis is specified by the draw:rotate-angle.

properties.name: RotationCenter
desc: This attribute specifies the position of the rotate center in terms of shape size fractions, if the property is omitted, then the geometrical center of the shape is used (this is the default).

properties.name: SecondLightDirection
desc: Specifies the direction of the second light.

properties.name: SecondLightHarsh
desc: Specifies if the secondary light is harsh.

properties.name: SecondLightLevel
desc: Specifies the intensity for the second light in percent.

properties.name: ShadeMode
desc: This property defines the shade mode.

properties.name: Shininess
desc: The draw:extrusion-shininess specifies the shininess of a mirror in percent.

properties.name: Skew
desc: The first value of the draw:extrusion-skew attribute specifies the skew amount of an extrusion in percent.
The second parameter specifies the skew-angle. Skew settings are only applied if the attribute ProjectionMode is ProjectionMode_PARALLEL.

properties.name: Specularity
desc: This attribute specifies the specularity of an extrusion object in percent.

properties.name: ViewPoint
desc: This attribute specifies the viewpoint of the observer.
